(ii) is subject to adequate secrecy provisions in the recipient jurisdiction; or
(j) disclose information for the purpose of, or otherwise in connection with, an audit required under section 5F of the Insurance Ordinance (Cap. 41) or section 16 of the Securities and Futures Ordinance (Cap. 571).
(2) A relevant authority may disclose information under subsection (1)(g) or (i) only if satisfied that it is desirable or expedient that the information should be disclosed, having regard to—
(a) the public interest and the interest of the investing public; and
(b) the recipient’s need for the information in performing the recipient’s functions.
(3) Despite section 76B—
(a) the Insurance Authority may—
(ii) disclose information to a Cap. 41 prescribed person for the purpose of enabling or assisting the Insurance Authority to discharge its functions under the Insurance Ordinance (Cap. 41); or
